    Scope and Contents
MENTAL HEALTH CARE PROJECT 
Albert McCarthy, administrator at the Jacksonville State Hospital, discusses his work and the changes in the functioning and operation of the hospital: clothing and laundry services, patients' trust funds, contractual services, the requisitioning process, the housekeeping department, hog farm and dairy operation, and the School of Nursing. 1 tape, 75 mins., 17 pp. 
Interview by Rodger Streitmatter, 1972 
